# EMBER - fork merge policy
#
# README.md is Ember's own front page (rebranded, bilingual, community links).
# Upstream Pumpkin's README lives at PUMPKIN_README.md, auto-refreshed by
# sync-upstream. Keep OUR README.md on every merge from master so upstream
# edits to README.md never produce a conflict.
#
# The `ours` merge driver is registered by scripts/sync-upstream.ps1
# (git config merge.ours.driver true). If you merge manually without that
# script, run that config command once first.
README.md merge=ours
